1
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:38,840
A perfect match. Truly a perfect match.

2
00:00:40,280 --> 00:00:41,159
Auntie.

3
00:00:41,200 --> 00:00:42,880
I'm counting on you for my child's matter.

4
00:00:43,079 --> 00:00:44,399
Don't worry.

5
00:00:44,679 --> 00:00:45,920
That young man.

6
00:00:46,039 --> 00:00:47,679
Is a university student.

7
00:00:47,880 --> 00:00:49,399
He's handsome.

8
00:00:49,399 --> 00:00:50,880
Good-looking with a great figure.

9
00:00:51,280 --> 00:00:52,240
The key thing is...

10
00:00:52,240 --> 00:00:54,520
He's also permanent staff at the factory.

11
00:00:55,479 --> 00:00:56,960
His prospects are really good.

12
00:00:57,880 --> 00:00:58,520
Mom.

13
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:00,079
I don't want to get married yet.

14
00:01:00,359 --> 00:01:01,039
Go, go, go.

15
00:01:01,200 --> 00:01:02,799
You're getting more and more out of line at home.

16
00:01:02,920 --> 00:01:04,799
I need to find you a husband's family to discipline you.

17
00:01:06,120 --> 00:01:06,760
Auntie.

18
00:01:07,120 --> 00:01:09,319
Tell me more about that young man's family.

19
00:01:09,599 --> 00:01:10,840
What else is there to know?

20
00:01:12,840 --> 00:01:14,239
That young man...

21
00:01:14,319 --> 00:01:16,840
He works at the factory.

22
00:01:17,280 --> 00:01:18,439
He's a nice person.

23
00:01:18,599 --> 00:01:19,480
The key thing is...

24
00:01:19,920 --> 00:01:21,680
He is also a...

25
00:01:21,959 --> 00:01:23,680
University student.

26
00:01:24,439 --> 00:01:26,159
Haven't you said all this already?

27
00:01:27,159 --> 00:01:28,079
Did I say that already?

28
00:01:31,480 --> 00:01:32,879
Meet... just meet him.

29
00:01:33,239 --> 00:01:34,799
It won't hurt just to meet him.

30
00:01:35,519 --> 00:01:35,719
This...

31
00:01:35,840 --> 00:01:37,079
This is too much.

32
00:01:37,200 --> 00:01:38,319
How can I accept this?

33
00:01:38,560 --> 00:01:39,599
It's only right. It's only right.

34
00:01:39,879 --> 00:01:41,680
Sister Sun, I'll trouble you then.

35
00:01:42,519 --> 00:01:43,719
You're welcome, you're welcome.

36
00:01:43,799 --> 00:01:44,319
Thank you.

37
00:01:44,319 --> 00:01:45,840
It's a good deed to bring people together.

38
00:01:45,840 --> 00:01:47,040
It's what I should do.

39
00:01:47,680 --> 00:01:48,840
Sister Sun.

40
00:01:49,280 --> 00:01:51,480
I've been waiting for you at home for a long time.

41
00:01:52,840 --> 00:01:54,680
Did you go to the wrong place?

42
00:01:58,040 --> 00:01:59,879
Look at my memory.

43
00:01:59,879 --> 00:02:01,799
Memory gets bad when you get old.

44
00:02:01,799 --> 00:02:03,280
It's over there, over there.

45
00:02:03,640 --> 00:02:04,239
Let's go, let's go.

46
00:02:04,359 --> 00:02:04,959
Let's talk at my place.

47
00:02:04,959 --> 00:02:05,480
Okay, okay, okay.

48
00:02:05,879 --> 00:02:07,159
You still want to marry off your daughter?

49
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:08,280
Whoever marries your daughter...

50
00:02:08,280 --> 00:02:09,360
Will have eight lifetimes of bad luck.

51
00:02:10,199 --> 00:02:11,560
Wait, wait for me.

52
00:02:11,759 --> 00:02:12,240
Pfft!

53
00:02:12,840 --> 00:02:14,000
You think just because your family has three men...

54
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:14,879
That you're something special?

55
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:16,159
Aren't they all just older bachelors?

56
00:02:16,560 --> 00:02:17,360
Which girl...

57
00:02:17,360 --> 00:02:18,879
Would marry your twice-married son-in-law?

58
00:02:19,199 --> 00:02:20,639
That would be shameful.

59
00:02:22,280 --> 00:02:22,919
Sister Sun.

60
00:02:22,919 --> 00:02:23,919
Have some water, have some water.

61
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:24,800
Don't be so polite.

62
00:02:25,280 --> 00:02:26,000
Is it that...

63
00:02:26,319 --> 00:02:28,159
You have a good girl in mind?

64
00:02:28,560 --> 00:02:30,520
That goes without saying.

65
00:02:31,039 --> 00:02:34,599
That girl is incredibly pretty.

66
00:02:34,719 --> 00:02:36,520
She has fine features.

67
00:02:36,919 --> 00:02:38,560
When she smiles, her eyes...

68
00:02:38,599 --> 00:02:39,960
Curve like crescents.

69
00:02:40,360 --> 00:02:41,120
Just looking at her...

70
00:02:41,280 --> 00:02:42,400
You know immediately...

71
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:44,599
She's a kind-hearted girl.

72
00:02:45,280 --> 00:02:47,560
She has an older sister who is already married.

73
00:02:47,879 --> 00:02:49,639
And a younger sister in high school.

74
00:02:49,639 --> 00:02:50,960
Who is about to take the college entrance exam.

75
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:52,120
She is ranked...

76
00:02:52,120 --> 00:02:53,199
Second.

77
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:54,159
In the future...

78
00:02:54,280 --> 00:02:56,120
Her family won't have any...

79
00:02:56,639 --> 00:02:58,479
Burdens.

80
00:03:01,479 --> 00:03:02,280
Sister Sun.

81
00:03:02,439 --> 00:03:04,240
Then arrange a meeting.

82
00:03:04,240 --> 00:03:04,879
Let's meet.

83
00:03:04,879 --> 00:03:06,159
Okay, okay.

84
00:03:08,120 --> 00:03:10,439
I'm about to have a daughter-in-law.

85
00:03:23,280 --> 00:03:24,360
Why are you here?

86
00:03:26,680 --> 00:03:27,879
What did you come here for?

87
00:03:30,039 --> 00:03:30,759
None of your business.

88
00:03:33,759 --> 00:03:34,520
About that...

89
00:03:35,520 --> 00:03:37,400
the pigweed and the pigsty.

90
00:03:37,560 --> 00:03:38,319
Thank you.

91
00:03:39,280 --> 00:03:40,879
I thought you were up to no good that day.

92
00:03:41,280 --> 00:03:42,080
The past couple of days,

93
00:03:42,199 --> 00:03:43,879
raising pigs the way you suggested,

94
00:03:44,319 --> 00:03:45,680
the pigs have really grown a lot.

95
00:03:46,599 --> 00:03:47,439
It was just a small favor.

96
00:03:48,560 --> 00:03:49,319
Besides,

97
00:03:50,439 --> 00:03:51,919
I helped you fix the pigsty

98
00:03:52,319 --> 00:03:53,680
because I was afraid your pigs would run loose

99
00:03:53,840 --> 00:03:54,800
and root up my family's vegetables.

100
00:03:55,680 --> 00:03:57,520
Then my mom would argue with me,

101
00:03:57,520 --> 00:03:58,240
and I'd get annoyed listening to it.

102
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:01,800
I knew you weren't that kind-hearted.

103
00:04:02,680 --> 00:04:03,639
Don't worry.

104
00:04:03,800 --> 00:04:05,400
I won't cause you any more trouble.

105
00:04:05,599 --> 00:04:06,240
And you won't have to

106
00:04:06,240 --> 00:04:07,919
be caught in the middle between me and your mom.

107
00:04:08,120 --> 00:04:08,639
I...

108
00:04:12,280 --> 00:04:13,639
I have to remind you,

109
00:04:14,240 --> 00:04:16,040
professional pig farming isn't simple.

110
00:04:16,399 --> 00:04:17,680
Just the content in the books alone

111
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:19,000
takes half a year to learn,

112
00:04:19,160 --> 00:04:21,000
or even a year to study and practice.

113
00:04:21,879 --> 00:04:23,639
Plus, meat prices fluctuate so much now.

114
00:04:23,920 --> 00:04:25,000
No one knows

115
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:26,759
how much money your pigs will make when sold.

116
00:04:27,240 --> 00:04:28,519
So if you really want to raise pigs,

117
00:04:29,079 --> 00:04:29,839
you have to study more.

118
00:04:30,399 --> 00:04:31,639
Otherwise, sell your piglets early on.

119
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:36,360
You just can't stand seeing our Wang family make money, right?

120
00:04:36,959 --> 00:04:38,759
Did your mom send you to talk me out of it?

121
00:04:39,160 --> 00:04:40,399
Let me tell you,

122
00:04:40,399 --> 00:04:41,680
my plan to make money raising pigs...

123
00:04:41,680 --> 00:04:43,639
I learned it from a master.

124
00:04:43,879 --> 00:04:45,759
That master is much better than you.

125
00:04:46,079 --> 00:04:47,319
You can't scare me.

126
00:04:48,560 --> 00:04:49,839
There is no master.

127
00:04:50,279 --> 00:04:51,600
I just told the grocery stall owner

128
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:53,040
about the idea of raising pigs.

129
00:04:53,639 --> 00:04:54,759
I didn't expect that actually doing it

130
00:04:54,959 --> 00:04:55,720
would be so troublesome.

131
00:04:56,839 --> 00:04:57,680
What?

132
00:05:00,360 --> 00:05:02,120
You told the grocery stall boss

133
00:05:02,120 --> 00:05:03,000
that raising pigs makes money?

134
00:05:03,279 --> 00:05:04,519
You are that master?

135
00:05:04,879 --> 00:05:05,360
So,

136
00:05:05,519 --> 00:05:07,480
you're treating me like a lab rat?

137
00:05:07,680 --> 00:05:09,519
I just mentioned the idea of raising pigs to him.

138
00:05:09,759 --> 00:05:10,480
Who told you

139
00:05:10,680 --> 00:05:12,000
to start doing it without studying at all?

140
00:05:12,240 --> 00:05:14,040
Now you're blaming me?

141
00:05:14,879 --> 00:05:16,000
I can't be bothered to argue with you.

142
00:05:16,519 --> 00:05:17,600
If you really can't raise them well,

143
00:05:17,879 --> 00:05:19,199
hurry up and sell your two pigs.

144
00:05:19,399 --> 00:05:20,800
Don't end up making no money

145
00:05:20,879 --> 00:05:22,000
and owing a mountain of debt.

146
00:05:25,480 --> 00:05:27,600
I got held up by something just now.

147
00:05:27,879 --> 00:05:29,319
You two are already chatting.

148
00:05:29,839 --> 00:05:30,519
How is it?

149
00:05:30,759 --> 00:05:32,680
Are you satisfied with each other?

150
00:05:34,639 --> 00:05:35,240
What?

151
00:05:37,399 --> 00:05:38,800
This... Auntie Sun,

152
00:05:39,279 --> 00:05:40,959
the blind date you mentioned...

153
00:05:42,360 --> 00:05:43,120
is her?

154
00:05:43,439 --> 00:05:44,240
That's right.

155
00:05:44,879 --> 00:05:45,759
I see

156
00:05:45,759 --> 00:05:47,759
you two are chatting quite happily.

157
00:05:48,040 --> 00:05:48,639
Why don't we

158
00:05:48,839 --> 00:05:50,879
find a chance to meet the parents?

159
00:05:51,560 --> 00:05:52,839
You want me to have a blind date with the Zheng family?

160
00:05:53,240 --> 00:05:54,439
Absolutely impossible!

161
00:05:54,480 --> 00:05:55,439
Yingrong,

162
00:05:55,439 --> 00:05:56,519
let's talk this over calmly.

163
00:05:58,600 --> 00:05:59,399
Minjiang,

164
00:05:59,439 --> 00:06:00,600
you're a grown man,

165
00:06:00,600 --> 00:06:01,639
hurry up and take the initiative!

166
00:06:03,079 --> 00:06:03,800
Auntie Sun,

167
00:06:05,160 --> 00:06:07,000
I have a family feud with Wang Yingrong.

168
00:06:07,439 --> 00:06:09,439
There is absolutely no way I'll be with her.

169
00:06:15,160 --> 00:06:16,959
The horoscopes match quite well!

170
00:06:17,720 --> 00:06:19,480
How could I have made a wrong match?

171
00:07:11,680 --> 00:07:12,120
This...

172
00:07:12,680 --> 00:07:13,519
Who did this?

173
00:07:14,199 --> 00:07:14,959
Me.

174
00:07:18,399 --> 00:07:19,839
Full of dirty tricks.

175
00:07:19,839 --> 00:07:21,160
Let's see if you can still pretend.

176
00:07:21,240 --> 00:07:22,360
Still trying to trick me?

177
00:07:22,560 --> 00:07:23,480
Serves you right.

178
00:07:25,199 --> 00:07:26,279
Wang Yingrong, you...

179
00:07:37,959 --> 00:07:40,040
Let's see if he dares to trick me again

180
00:07:41,199 --> 00:07:42,279
Selling fish was his idea

181
00:07:42,279 --> 00:07:43,600
Selling pigs was his idea too

182
00:07:43,879 --> 00:07:45,040
Some "master"

183
00:07:45,319 --> 00:07:46,639
Does he think he can talk without consequences?

184
00:07:47,839 --> 00:07:49,240
So he doesn't put up a single cent

185
00:07:49,240 --> 00:07:50,000
Just moves his lips

186
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:51,160
And I'm the one charging into battle

187
00:07:52,279 --> 00:07:53,079
How was I supposed to know?

188
00:07:53,199 --> 00:07:55,360
He said that specifically to you?

189
00:07:55,839 --> 00:07:58,199
How can you trust a Mr. Know-it-all?

190
00:07:59,800 --> 00:08:01,199
At least about him being a master...

191
00:08:01,279 --> 00:08:02,160
I didn't lie to you

192
00:08:02,680 --> 00:08:03,680
Just look at our market

193
00:08:03,680 --> 00:08:04,959
No matter whose stuff is broken...

194
00:08:05,120 --> 00:08:05,839
...they all look for Master Zheng

195
00:08:06,040 --> 00:08:06,839
He can fix it all

196
00:08:06,839 --> 00:08:08,160
It's a piece of cake for him

197
00:08:08,839 --> 00:08:09,720
He's not just a master

198
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:10,759
He's a miracle worker

199
00:08:11,160 --> 00:08:12,279
That part is true

200
00:08:13,160 --> 00:08:14,519
Some miracle worker

201
00:08:15,160 --> 00:08:16,759
A technician who fixes pigsties

202
00:08:17,199 --> 00:08:18,360
The business tips he came up with...

203
00:08:18,360 --> 00:08:20,120
...did you treat them like a secret manual?

204
00:08:21,079 --> 00:08:22,680
So you're going to keep raising pigs?

205
00:08:23,240 --> 00:08:24,040
What else can I do?

206
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:25,639
The pigs are already at home

207
00:08:25,639 --> 00:08:26,920
I'm definitely raising them to the end

208
00:08:27,160 --> 00:08:28,639
Can I let people look down on me?

209
00:08:29,839 --> 00:08:30,759
Especially not let a...

210
00:08:30,759 --> 00:08:32,600
...darn blind date look down on me

211
00:08:33,879 --> 00:08:35,679
What darn blind date?

212
00:08:41,440 --> 00:08:41,960
Xiaohei

213
00:08:42,240 --> 00:08:42,799
Come here

214
00:08:46,320 --> 00:08:47,120
Sister Yingrong

215
00:08:47,480 --> 00:08:48,360
Who is this?

216
00:08:48,480 --> 00:08:49,480
Xiaohei from the countryside

217
00:08:49,679 --> 00:08:50,879
He's the teacher teaching me to raise pigs

218
00:08:51,039 --> 00:08:51,440
Let's go

219
00:08:51,919 --> 00:08:52,200
Okay

220
00:09:03,159 --> 00:09:04,120
Who is that?

221
00:09:04,600 --> 00:09:05,720
A new blind date?

222
00:09:06,480 --> 00:09:08,120
Why are you also saying blind date?

223
00:09:08,480 --> 00:09:10,720
That's her teacher from the countryside who teaches her pig raising

224
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:11,720
Countryside?

225
00:09:12,360 --> 00:09:13,600
What is she up to now?

226
00:09:16,919 --> 00:09:17,720
Forget it

227
00:09:18,159 --> 00:09:19,840
Let her do whatever she wants

228
00:09:20,080 --> 00:09:21,120
She knows, yet she still chooses this

229
00:09:21,799 --> 00:09:22,679
It's not my fault

230
00:09:23,960 --> 00:09:24,679
Of course

231
00:09:25,360 --> 00:09:26,039
Never mind her

232
00:09:26,639 --> 00:09:27,919
The darn blind date, I suppose

233
00:09:33,080 --> 00:09:33,879
Come take a look up front

234
00:09:35,240 --> 00:09:36,159
Look at the pigs we raise

235
00:09:36,480 --> 00:09:37,000
So fat

236
00:09:37,960 --> 00:09:38,480
Yeah

237
00:09:38,799 --> 00:09:39,919
Look, over here too

238
00:09:41,159 --> 00:09:42,279
Take a look at our feed

239
00:09:44,080 --> 00:09:45,960
The pigs love this feed

240
00:09:49,360 --> 00:09:49,919
Come, come

241
00:09:53,960 --> 00:09:55,200
Our feed is...

242
00:09:55,320 --> 00:09:56,080
...eighty percent dry feed...

243
00:09:56,399 --> 00:09:57,159
...and only twenty percent water

244
00:09:57,320 --> 00:09:58,519
So the pigs really enjoy eating it

245
00:10:00,480 --> 00:10:01,879
Local pigs only eat highland barley feed

246
00:10:01,879 --> 00:10:03,000
They won't eat any other feed

247
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:03,679
Exactly

248
00:10:03,840 --> 00:10:04,919
If you want to raise them well...

249
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:06,200
...there are many things to watch out for

250
00:10:06,279 --> 00:10:07,360
Thank you both

251
00:10:07,559 --> 00:10:08,399
If it weren't for you...

252
00:10:08,399 --> 00:10:10,759
...I wouldn't know how to raise my two pigs properly

253
00:10:11,480 --> 00:10:12,360
You're welcome

254
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:14,600
I actually wanted to ask if your village...

255
00:10:14,799 --> 00:10:15,600
...your village...

256
00:10:15,600 --> 00:10:17,559
...could rent me a place to raise pigs?

257
00:10:18,039 --> 00:10:18,480
Also...

258
00:10:18,720 --> 00:10:20,200
...who did you sell these pigs to?

259
00:10:20,279 --> 00:10:21,080
How much was it?

260
00:10:37,279 --> 00:10:38,480
I just came to the countryside

261
00:10:38,480 --> 00:10:40,120
to breathe some fresh air

262
00:10:40,120 --> 00:10:41,000
and catch a breeze.

263
00:10:44,120 --> 00:10:46,080
As for the stupid things some people do,

264
00:10:46,480 --> 00:10:47,480
I couldn't care less.

265
00:10:48,919 --> 00:10:49,720
Stop!

266
00:10:49,720 --> 00:10:51,039
Don't let her get away!

267
00:10:51,240 --> 00:10:52,039
Stop!

268
00:10:52,279 --> 00:10:53,759
Trying to steal our business?

269
00:10:53,960 --> 00:10:54,559
Don't run!

270
00:10:54,559 --> 00:10:56,120
Daring to target our village!

271
00:10:56,120 --> 00:10:56,879
I won't ask anymore!

272
00:10:56,879 --> 00:10:57,360
Stop chasing me!

273
00:10:57,360 --> 00:10:58,639
I won't ask anymore!

274
00:10:58,639 --> 00:10:59,399
Beat her!

275
00:10:59,679 --> 00:11:00,279
Zheng Minjiang!

276
00:11:00,440 --> 00:11:01,320
Trying to steal our business!

277
00:11:01,320 --> 00:11:01,960
Stop!

278
00:11:02,240 --> 00:11:03,840
Daring to come to our village and cause trouble!

279
00:11:03,919 --> 00:11:04,919
Don't just stand there, let's go!

280
00:11:04,919 --> 00:11:05,480
Get in!

281
00:11:05,919 --> 00:11:06,559
Stop!

282
00:11:06,559 --> 00:11:07,120
Quick, quick, quick!

283
00:11:07,519 --> 00:11:08,960
Hurry, go, go, go!

284
00:11:09,080 --> 00:11:09,519
Chase them!

285
00:11:09,519 --> 00:11:10,080
Quick, quick, quick!

286
00:11:10,080 --> 00:11:10,960
Catch her!

287
00:11:10,960 --> 00:11:11,519
Hurry up!

288
00:11:11,519 --> 00:11:12,399
Catch her!

289
00:11:12,440 --> 00:11:13,279
Go after them!

290
00:11:13,720 --> 00:11:14,399
Hurry up and chase them!

291
00:11:14,799 --> 00:11:15,559
Don't run!

292
00:11:16,480 --> 00:11:17,240
Don't run!

293
00:11:17,240 --> 00:11:17,840
Stop!

294
00:11:18,279 --> 00:11:18,960
Catch her!

295
00:11:23,080 --> 00:11:24,879
Did you come just to laugh at me?

296
00:11:25,519 --> 00:11:26,320
You...

297
00:11:27,120 --> 00:11:28,279
Who was it that saved you just now?

298
00:11:28,799 --> 00:11:29,679
If it weren't for me...

299
00:11:30,080 --> 00:11:30,360
You...

300
00:11:30,360 --> 00:11:31,080
What?

301
00:11:32,600 --> 00:11:34,879
I think they were just trying to scare me.

302
00:11:35,240 --> 00:11:36,759
What could they do to a girl anyway?

303
00:11:38,240 --> 00:11:39,080
Blockhead.

304
00:11:40,159 --> 00:11:40,919
What did you say?

305
00:11:44,200 --> 00:11:45,440
You go asking them for experience,

306
00:11:45,919 --> 00:11:46,919
trying to rent their site,

307
00:11:46,919 --> 00:11:48,000
and asking this and that.

308
00:11:51,240 --> 00:11:53,200
They see you're clearly trying to steal their business.

309
00:11:53,799 --> 00:11:55,399
It'd be a miracle if the villagers tolerated you.

310
00:11:55,759 --> 00:11:57,399
Don't be a wise guy after the fact.

311
00:11:58,480 --> 00:11:59,320
You really are...

312
00:11:59,879 --> 00:12:01,519
I came to save you out of the kindness of my heart.

313
00:12:02,360 --> 00:12:03,000
Besides,

314
00:12:03,879 --> 00:12:05,480
I can't just ignore you when you fall into a pit.

315
00:12:07,360 --> 00:12:08,399
That pit you're talking about,

316
00:12:08,399 --> 00:12:10,080
as if you weren't the one who dug it.

317
00:12:10,360 --> 00:12:11,000
Enough.

318
00:12:11,679 --> 00:12:13,120
I'll only fall for that trap once.

319
00:12:13,480 --> 00:12:14,720
From now on, you do your thing,

320
00:12:14,759 --> 00:12:15,679
and I'll do mine.

321
00:12:15,919 --> 00:12:16,919
Don't come and interfere with me.

322
00:12:46,639 --> 00:12:47,320
Where are you going?

323
00:12:48,080 --> 00:12:48,679
I'll give you a ride.

324
00:12:49,200 --> 00:12:50,000
No need.

325
00:12:56,480 --> 00:12:57,600
Blockhead.

326
00:13:00,279 --> 00:13:01,320
Fine, walk then.

327
00:13:10,320 --> 00:13:11,120
Get in.

328
00:13:21,639 --> 00:13:22,799
Get in.

329
00:13:25,919 --> 00:13:26,720
With those feet of yours,

330
00:13:27,399 --> 00:13:28,519
they'll be ruined by the time you get home.

331
00:13:28,879 --> 00:13:29,559
None of your business.

332
00:13:29,600 --> 00:13:30,399
Don't move.

333
00:13:38,080 --> 00:13:38,480
I...

334
00:13:40,679 --> 00:13:41,759
This habit of being stubborn,

335
00:13:42,559 --> 00:13:44,080
hasn't changed since we were kids.
